<D>__{i swear to god charlie, it's the truth.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<C>__{flashback}
<L>__{exterior street late afternoon}
<A>__{johnny boy is walking along the street. it is rush hour and the traffic is heavy. a shiny, late model car stops parallel to johnny boy. the young boy (sal) signals him by blowing the horn. (note that in the flashback, johnny boy's face is not bruised.)}
<C>__{sal}
<D>__{hey johnny, where're you goin'?}
<C>__{johnny boy}
<D>__{sal!... fourteen street.}
<C>__{sal}
<D>__{come on.}
<L>__{interior inside car late afternoon}
<C>__{johnny boy}
<D>__{this is some boat. your father's?}
<C>__{sal}
<D>__{yeah...just had it delivered...}
<C>__{johnny boy}
<D>__{hey... you got stereo.}
<C>__{sal}
<D>__{yeah, i think so.}
<A>__{as johnny boy admires the gadgets in the car he notices that sal is becoming very nervous.}
